## Project conventions

- **Language version:** {{e.g. Node 20 LTS / Python 3.13 / Go 1.24}}
- **Package manager:** {{npm | pnpm | yarn | bun | uv | poetry}}
- **Formatter / linter:** {{e.g. prettier + eslint / black + ruff / gofmt + golangci-lint}}
- **Test framework:** {{e.g. vitest / pytest / go test}}
- **Commit style:** Conventional Commits (see `CONTRIBUTING.md` if present)

## Architecture

{{2-4 bullets describing the high-level layout. Example:}}

- `src/app/` — Next.js App Router pages and layouts
- `src/components/` — reusable React components
- `src/lib/` — pure helpers and domain logic
- `src/server/` — server-only code (tRPC, DB access)

## Stack-specific rules

{{List any non-obvious constraints a contributor must know. Example:}}

- Server Components are the default; only add `'use client'` when truly needed.
- Database access goes through `src/server/db.ts` — never import the ORM directly in components.
- Never commit `.env.local`; use `.env.example` as the source of truth for expected keys.

## External services

{{List auth/payment/email/AI services the project depends on. Example:}}

- Supabase — auth + PostgreSQL
- Stripe — payments (test keys in dev, live keys via Vercel env)
- OpenAI — LLM calls behind `src/server/ai.ts` adapter

## Globals applied on top

This project inherits the user-level rules at `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` and the
global rule set at `~/.claude/rules/`. The project-specific rules live at
`.claude/rules/` (see that directory for details).

## What to do if things break

- **Undo last change** — Claude will restore from the most recent checkpoint commit.
- **Go back to the last working state** — Claude will find the last `CHECKPOINT: ... Status: WORKING` commit and restore files from it.
- **Something broke** — Claude will diagnose and fix silently per `rules/03-error-recovery.md`.

